nspired last-minute Halloween costume ideas ft Janhvi Kapoor to Katrina Kaif as Harley Quinn  More than just innerwear, Jockey Woman's new collection is an invitation to self-care, love, and quiet celebration  Kareena Kapoor Khan just roared in a Sabyasachi Leopard print saree and we are obsessed  Red outfit Inspiration for Karva Chauth 2025: Alia Bhatt to Aishwarya Rai Bachchan  6 celeb-inspired couple fashion for Diwali party 2025: Ranbir Kapoor-Alia Bhatt to Vicky Kaushal-Katrina Kaif  Sonam Kapoor serves boho maternity vibes, but her elephant bag steals the show  Meet celebrity hairstylist who charges Rs 20,000- Rs 50,000 per haircut; Kajal Aggarwal, Dino Morea and others swear by him  Suhana Khan oozes glam in Rs 2,95,000 gown while Ananya Panday dazzles in Rs 78,000 rhinestone dress at Ba***ds of Bollywood premiere  Alia Bhatt looks HOT in Tom Ford's iconic Gucci dress from 1996 without overdoing it, styled by Rhea Kapoor  Gulshan Devaiah has shared his thoughts on Vinesh Phogat's request for a joint silver medal at the Paris Olympics 2024 if she is\\u00a0unable to compete for the gold. The Ulajh actor expressed that it would be \\\"unfair\\\" to other athletes who faced disqualification under similar conditions.  The news of Indian wrestlerVinesh Phogat's disqualification from the Paris Olympics 2024 has been making waves on the internet since Wednesday. Meanwhile, Bollywood actor Gulshan Devaiah took to his social media handles and shared a unique response on granting her a silver medal.  He stated, \\\"Emotionally I hope an appeal is accepted & Vinesh is awarded the Silver but I also feel it's unfair on every other athlete who's been disqualified earlier under the same circumstances. I am deciding to accept it and move on but it's not really about how I feel. This must be unimaginable devastating on Vinesh & her team.\\\"  \\\"As a fellow Indian, I say thank you champ!!!\\u00a0 Be Well (accompanied by hand raised emoji) VandeMataram (accompanied by folded hand emojis),\\\" he further added.      For the unversed, following her disqualification from the Paris Olympics 2024, Vinesh Phogat appealed to the Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS) for permission to compete for the gold medal. If that is not granted, she requested to be awarded a joint silver medal. CAS is expected to provide an interim ruling on Thursday, with the possibility of overturning the original decision.  Meanwhile, actor-turned-politician,Hema Malinireacting to the decision also suggested one to keep their weight in check. In her first media interaction outside the Parliament, Malini on Wednesday called it \\\"surprising\\\" and \\\"so strange\\\" that Phogat was disqualified for being 100 gms above the limit.  \\\"Kitna mehatwa hain apna weight aur wazan ko theek se rakhna! Hum sab ko isse ek achha seekh milna chahiye sab kalakaro ko, mahilayon ko sabko\\u2026 ki (It is important to keep the weight in check. It is a lesson for all of us that) 100 gm also matters a lot! We feel very sad for her. I wish she loses that 100 grams quickly lekin milega nahi abhi (but she would not get an opportunity),\\\" she had said.  ALSO READ:Vinesh Phogat disqualified from Paris Olympics 2024 Finals: PM Narendra Modi, Ranveer Singh, Alia Bhatt, Anushka Sharma and more call her 'gold'\"}"